  "prompt": "Who is Amartya Sen?",
  "response": "Amartya Sen is an Indian economist and philosopher, born on November 3, 1933, in Santiniketan, West Bengal, India. He is best known for his contributions to development economics, social choice theory, and welfare economics. Sen was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences in 1998 for his work on famine, human development theory, and poverty.\n\nSen's most notable works include \"Poverty and Famines: An Essay on Entitlement and Deprivation\" (1981), \"Development as Freedom\" (1999), and \"The Idea of Justice\" (2009). He introduced the concept of \"capability approach,\" which focuses on the importance of enhancing individual freedoms and capabilities as a means to improve human development.\n\nThroughout his career, Sen has held academic positions at various prestigious institutions, including the University of Calcutta, the London School of Economics, Harvard University, and currently, as a Professor of Economics and Philosophy at Harvard University. He has also been actively involved in policy-making and has served as an advisor to several international organizations, including the United Nations and the World Bank.",
